mergence of new global challenges like Islamic extremism and international terrorism. Brands reveals how deep structural changes in the international system interacted with strategies pursued by Jimmy Carter, Ronald Reagan, and George H. W. Bush to usher in an era of reinvigorated and in many ways unprecedented American primacy. Making the Unipolar Moment provides an indispensable account of how the post–Cold War order that we still inhabit came to be.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aDiplomatic relations. 0aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Government / International. 0aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSecurity Studies. 4aU.S. History.  apolitical strategy, Ronald Reagan, George H.W. Bush, globalization, international terrorism, Jimmy Carter, George Shultz.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170343040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501703430423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501703430/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles